subject: Re: [junit] Cryptic Clues
msgSnippet: By Rose model, you simply mean UML diagrams, sequence diagrams, etc.  Correct?  If so, use a tool to create the diagrams from the code or class files.  I think
messageBody:
By Rose model, you simply mean UML diagrams, sequence
diagrams, etc. Correct? If so, use a tool to create
the diagrams from the code or class files. I think
Rational already does this. Are you using their
development tools? If I have misunderstood, sorry.

-jason

P.S. no offense meant by the former email, just trying
to get you be more specific

--- Pankaj Solanki <psolanki@...> wrote:
> How best we can define and incorporate the
> functionalities of JUnit in a
> Rose Model ?
> Isn't it a bit less cryptic this time (hmmm !!!)
>
> -pankaj
